  "body": "### Description\r\nWith https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/4857 if there is a mention in the text input it is not possible to have the cursor inside a mention, as well as when pointing to a mention with the mouse, this is treated as a link. However this is not the case when text that contains a mention is copied and then pasted to the text input.\r\n\r\n1) the positions of the mentions in the clipboard text should be somehow stored so that the cursor jumps over the mention\r\n2) when text is pasted and due to it being a rich text containing a link, the text is decorated to be underlined by default, this underline should be removed (try something like `var plainText = messageInputField.getFormattedText(0, messageInputField.length).replace(/text-decoration: underline;/g, \" \") .replace(/span style=\\\"/g, \"span style=\\\"text-decoration:none; \");`",
